- 17% = 5.95% + 7.15% + (IH and LBP)  
- 17% - 5.95% - 7.15% = 3.90% have both IH and LBP.  

The percentage with low blood pressure and irregular heartbeat is 3.90%. Therefore, the percentage with low blood pressure and regular heartbeat (not IH) is:  
- Total LBP - (LBP and IH) = 19% - 3.90% = 15.10%.  

