  - \( P(S = 9) = \binom{10}{9} (0.7)^9 (0.3) \approx 0.121060821 \),
  - \( P(S = 10) = (0.7)^{10} \approx 0.0282475249 \),
  - \( P(S = 9) + P(S = 10) \approx 0.1493083459 \),
  - \( P(S \leq 8) \approx 1 - 0.1493083459 = 0.8506916541 \).
- Then, \( [P(S \leq 8)]^3 \approx (0.8506916541)^3 \approx 0.615625 \).
- Thus, \( P(\max(S_1, S_2, S_3) > 8) = 1 - 0.615625 = 0.384375 \).
- Rounded to three significant figures, this probability is 0.384.

The final answer is a probability, and no units are specified beyond the numerical value.

