Solution: The problem involves finding the limit of the probability of no matches as the number of balls \(n\) increases without bound. A match occurs when the ball numbered \(m\) is selected on the \(m\)-th draw. The probability of no matches for \(n\) balls is given by the number of derangements (permutations with no fixed points) divided by \(n!\), which is \(\sum_{i=0}^{n} \frac{(-1)^i}{i!}\).

