- For \(\frac{1}{3} < X < \frac{2}{3}\), the condition does not hold.

The probability is the length of the intervals where the condition holds: \([0, \frac{1}{3}]\) and \([\frac{2}{3}, 1]\), each of length \(\frac{1}{3}\), so the total probability is \(\frac{2}{3}\).

